This paper deals with the analysis of a distributed system with identical agents and control policies, which falls under the category of "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). The paper also uses transfer functions to analyze the bidirectional control, which is a common technique in "Mathematical Physics" (cs.MA) and "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the stability of the system, which is a topic in "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
